"This project focuses on predicting Alzheimer's disease using an Artificial Neural Network. I first preprocessed the patient dataset by handling missing values, encoding categorical variables, scaling numerical features, and splitting the data into training and testing sets. I then built an ANN with dense layers using ReLU activation and a sigmoid output layer for binary classification. The model was trained using the Adam optimizer and binary cross-entropy loss, and its performance was evaluated using metrics such as accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score, and a confusion matrix. The aim is to assist clinicians in identifying patients who may be at risk of Alzheimer's disease at an early stage, enabling timely medical intervention."
